posts.summary:
I'm pleased to announce the launch of the DeBank Stats project!

What is this?
A snapshot of your DeBank account stream and an analysis of up to 100 recent posts. The report contains two tables that provide information about the popularity of posts and the most active users. The users' table is a perfect tool for finding accounts to unfollow if you are close to the 1k limit.

Below is the description of the most useful features and how to request the report.

The project's home page and report examples can be found here:
https://vermi321.github.io/debank-stats/

Since version 1.6 DeBank helper extension supports opening posts in a new tab via Cmd/Ctrl + click 😉 So hurry up to update it and start using it! More about the extension: https://debank.com/stream/531856

#Proposal for @DeBank:

Please implement the feature natively.

Also, it doesn't seem like you "receive" all the approvals, some of them are simply missed e.g. https://debank.com/stream/538280 in most cases it happens when you take a few days break of receiving approvals, and then just go from the top of the list and stop on the middle leaving the oldest one untouched.

Unlike my previous free tools, this one won't be free due to the time invested in its development and the time I'd still need to spend on generating reports, if there's demand of course 😁
